postcolonial and transnational studies, making important intertextual connections and foregrounding links to prevailing theoretical and speculative scholarship. The work's introduction argues that irony is central to Ghosh's vision and discusses the importance of the concepts of "testimony" and "history" to Ghosh's narratives. An invaluable interview with Amitav Ghosh discusses individual works and the author's overall philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aAsian Studies : Asian Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Indic.2bisacsh1 aBhautoo-Dewnarain, Nandini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoh, Robbie B. H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuttunen, Tuomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuo, Shao-Pin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPillai, Shanthini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamraj, Ruby S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRatté, Lou, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSankaran, Chitra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSankaran, Chitra, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTalib, Ismail S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaylor, Crystal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVernerey, Tammy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZullo, Federica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781438441825?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degr